{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013BhXjYHRvebUYzJcW7wGC7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→title: 'Verification Tier Rework'\n     3→slug: 'verification-tier-rework'\n     4→created: '2026-03-26'\n     5→status: 'ready-for-dev'\n     6→stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n     7→tech_stack: ['typescript', 'vitest']\n     8→files_to_modify:\n     9→  - commands/harness-run.md\n    10→  - src/modules/verify/types.ts\n    11→  - src/modules/verify/parser.ts\n    12→  - src/modules/verify/proof.ts\n    13→  - src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts\n    14→  - src/modules/verify/validation-runner.ts\n    15→  - src/modules/verify/validation-runner-types.ts\n    16→  - patches/dev/enforcement.md\n    17→  - patches/review/enforcement.md\n    18→  - patches/verify/story-verification.md\n    19→  - knowledge/verification-patterns.md\n    20→code_patterns:\n    21→  - 'Replace 3 overlapping systems with single VerificationTier enum'\n    22→  - 'Story tier = max(AC tiers) — highest tier wins'\n    23→  - 'Tier determines verification method, not the other way around'\n    24→test_patterns:\n    25→  - 'Update classifyStrategy tests to use new tier names'\n    26→  - 'Test tier derivation from AC tags'\n    27→  - 'Test each verification path dispatches correctly'\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→# Tech-Spec: Verification Tier Rework\n    31→\n    32→**Created:** 2026-03-26\n    33→\n    34→## Overview\n    35→\n    36→### Problem Statement\n    37→\n    38→Codeharness has three overlapping, disconnected verification classification systems:\n    39→1. `Verifiability` type: `'cli-verifiable' | 'integration-required'` (per-AC, in `verify/types.ts`)\n    40→2. `VerificationStrategy`: `'docker' | 'escalate'` (per-AC, from `classifyStrategy()` in `verify/parser.ts`)\n    41→3. `verification-tier` HTML comment: `'unit-testable'` or default black-box (per-story, manual tag)\n    42→\n    43→The naming confuses mechanism (Docker, CLI, unit-test) with what's being proven. Agents guess which tier to use — sometimes wrong (tried Docker for a pure test-provable story). No clear criteria exist beyond vague prompt text.\n    44→\n    45→### Solution\n    46→\n    47→Replace all three systems with one `VerificationTier` enum based on what evidence is needed to prove the ACs work:\n    48→\n    49→| Tier | What it proves | How to verify | Examples |\n    50→|------|---------------|---------------|----------|\n    51→| `test-provable` | Code structure + passing tests = sufficient | Build, run tests, grep/read code. No running app. | Refactoring, type changes, new utility functions, test additions, config changes, documentation |\n    52→| `runtime-provable` | Running the built artifact = sufficient | Build → run binary/server → interact → check output. Local execution. | CLI commands, API endpoints, file processors, REPL behavior |\n    53→| `environment-provable` | Full environment with services = needed | Docker stack, databases, message queues, observability. | Observability integration, distributed workflows, data pipelines, multi-service interactions |\n    54→| `escalate` | Cannot be proven automatically | Human judgment, hardware, paid services. | GPU rendering, visual inspection, physical device testing |\n    55→\n    56→Story-level tier is auto-derived: highest tier among all ACs wins. No manual tagging.\n    57→\n    58→## Context for Development\n    59→\n    60→### Codebase Patterns\n    61→\n    62→Current system locations:\n    63→- `src/modules/verify/types.ts` L10: `type Verifiability = 'cli-verifiable' | 'integration-required'`\n    64→- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` L84: `classifyStrategy()` returns `'docker' | 'escalate'`\n    65→- `src/modules/verify/proof.ts` L116: checks `unit-testable` string in proof `**Tier:**` line\n    66→- `commands/harness-run.md` L263: checks `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` HTML comment\n    67→- `commands/harness-run.md` L158: create-story prompt tells agent to add `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` per AC\n    68→\n    69→### Files to Reference\n    70→\n    71→| File | Purpose | What changes |\n    72→| ---- | ------- | ------------ |\n    73→| `src/modules/verify/types.ts` | `Verifiability` type | Replace with `VerificationTier` enum |\n    74→| `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` | `classifyStrategy()`, `classifyVerifiability()`, `parseVerificationTag()` | Rewrite to use new tiers + clear keyword matching |\n    75→| `src/modules/verify/proof.ts` | Checks `**Tier:** unit-testable` in proofs | Update to check new tier names |\n    76→| `src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts` | Groups ACs by verifiability | Use new tier |\n    77→| `src/modules/verify/validation-runner.ts` | Runs verification per tier | Dispatch on new tiers |\n    78→| `src/modules/verify/validation-runner-types.ts` | Runner type definitions | Update tier references |\n    79→| `commands/harness-run.md` | Step 3a (create-story AC tagging) + Step 3d (verification dispatch) | Rewrite both with new tiers, criteria, examples |\n    80→| `patches/dev/enforcement.md` | Dev workflow enforcement | Update tier references |\n    81→| `patches/review/enforcement.md` | Review workflow enforcement | Update tier references |\n    82→| `patches/verify/story-verification.md` | Verification enforcement | Update tier references |\n    83→| `knowledge/verification-patterns.md` | Agent knowledge about verification | Rewrite with new tier guide |\n    84→\n    85→### Technical Decisions\n    86→\n    87→- **Single enum:** `VerificationTier = 'test-provable' | 'runtime-provable' | 'environment-provable' | 'escalate'`\n    88→- **Per-AC tagging stays:** `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` etc. But the tag is now one of the four tiers, not a different vocabulary.\n    89→- **Story tier = max(AC tiers):** If any AC is `environment-provable`, the story is `environment-provable`. If all ACs are `test-provable`, the story is `test-provable`. Hierarchy: `escalate > environment-provable > runtime-provable > test-provable`.\n    90→- **No manual story-level tag:** Remove `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`. The story tier is DERIVED from its ACs automatically by `harness-run` Step 3d.\n    91→- **`classifyStrategy()` removed:** Replaced by `classifyTier(description: string): VerificationTier` which uses clear keyword matching.\n    92→- **Tier criteria for create-story agent:** The harness-run prompt includes explicit decision tree with examples so the agent tags consistently.\n    93→- **Backward compat:** Old tags (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`) map to new tiers during parsing. No story file migration needed.\n    94→\n    95→## Implementation Plan\n    96→\n    97→### Tasks\n    98→\n    99→- [ ] Task 1: Define new `VerificationTier` type and update `types.ts`\n   100→  - File: `src/modules/verify/types.ts`\n   101→  - Action: Replace `Verifiability = 'cli-verifiable' | 'integration-required'` with `VerificationTier = 'test-provable' | 'runtime-provable' | 'environment-provable' | 'escalate'`. Add `TIER_HIERARCHY` const for tier ordering. Add `maxTier(tiers: VerificationTier[]): VerificationTier` utility. Add backward compat mapping: `'cli-verifiable' → 'test-provable'`, `'integration-required' → 'environment-provable'`, `'unit-testable' → 'test-provable'`.\n   102→\n   103→- [ ] Task 2: Rewrite `parser.ts` tier classification\n   104→  - File: `src/modules/verify/parser.ts`\n   105→  - Action: Replace `classifyStrategy()` with `classifyTier(description: string): VerificationTier`. Replace `classifyVerifiability()` with tier-based logic. Update `parseVerificationTag()` to read new tag format `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` with backward compat for old tags. Update `parseStoryACs()` to return `VerificationTier` per AC. Clear keyword lists:\n   106→    - `test-provable`: \"file exists\", \"export\", \"type\", \"interface\", \"test passes\", \"line count\", \"coverage\", \"refactor\", \"rename\", \"documentation\"\n   107→    - `runtime-provable`: \"CLI command\", \"API endpoint\", \"HTTP\", \"server\", \"output shows\", \"exit code\", \"binary\", \"runs and produces\"\n   108→    - `environment-provable`: \"Docker\", \"container\", \"observability\", \"telemetry\", \"database\", \"queue\", \"distributed\", \"multi-service\", \"end-to-end\"\n   109→    - `escalate`: \"physical hardware\", \"human visual\", \"paid service\", \"GPU\", \"manual inspection\"\n   110→\n   111→- [ ] Task 3: Update proof validation\n   112→  - File: `src/modules/verify/proof.ts`\n   113→  - Action: Update `**Tier:**` parsing (L116) to recognize all four tier names. Update enforcement skip logic: `test-provable` and `runtime-provable` skip Docker enforcement. Only `environment-provable` requires Docker evidence.\n   114→\n   115→- [ ] Task 4: Update validation ACs and runner\n   116→  - Files: `src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts`, `validation-runner.ts`, `validation-runner-types.ts`\n   117→  - Action: Replace all `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required` references with new tier names. Update grouping logic to group by tier instead of binary verifiability.\n   118→\n   119→- [ ] Task 5: Rewrite harness-run verification dispatch (Step 3d)\n   120→  - File: `commands/harness-run.md`\n   121→  - Action: Replace the binary `unit-testable` vs `black-box` dispatch with four-tier dispatch:\n   122→    - **Step 3d-0:** Parse all AC tags from story file. Derive story tier = `maxTier(all AC tiers)`.\n   123→    - **test-provable:** Subagent runs build + tests + code inspection. No running app. No Docker.\n   124→    - **runtime-provable:** Subagent builds artifact, runs it locally, interacts with it, checks behavior. No Docker stack needed but may run the binary.\n   125→    - **environment-provable:** Full Docker verification (existing black-box flow).\n   126→    - **escalate:** Mark ACs as escalated, check if remaining non-escalated ACs pass. If all non-escalated pass, story is done with escalated notes.\n   127→\n   128→- [ ] Task 6: Update create-story prompt with tier criteria\n   129→  - File: `commands/harness-run.md` (Step 3a)\n   130→  - Action: Replace the current vague AC tagging instruction with explicit decision tree:\n   131→    ```\n   132→    For each AC, determine the verification tier:\n   133→\n   134→    Is this AC about code structure, types, file existence, test passing, or documentation?\n   135→    → test-provable\n   136→\n   137→    Does this AC require running the built application and checking its output/behavior?\n   138→    → runtime-provable\n   139→\n   140→    Does this AC require Docker, databases, observability stack, or multiple services?\n   141→    → environment-provable\n   142→\n   143→    Does this AC require physical hardware, human visual judgment, or paid external services?\n   144→    → escalate\n   145→\n   146→    Tag: <!-- verification: {tier} -->\n   147→\n   148→    EXAMPLES:\n   149→    - \"Given function X exists, when called with Y, then returns Z\" → test-provable (unit test proves it)\n   150→    - \"Given the CLI is run with --flag, when output is checked, then it shows X\" → runtime-provable (need to run the binary)\n   151→    - \"Given the server is running, when POST /api/users is called, then logs appear in VictoriaLogs\" → environment-provable (needs observability stack)\n   152→    - \"Given the game renders at 60fps on a 4K display\" → escalate (needs GPU hardware)\n   153→    ```\n   154→\n   155→- [ ] Task 7: Update knowledge and enforcement docs\n   156→  - Files: `knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, `patches/review/enforcement.md`, `patches/verify/story-verification.md`\n   157→  - Action: Replace all old tier terminology with new. Add tier decision guide to knowledge file.\n   158→\n   159→- [ ] Task 8: Update all tests\n   160→  - Files: `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`, `validation-acs.test.ts`, `verify.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`, etc.\n   161→  - Action: Update all tier references. Update `classifyStrategy` tests to `classifyTier`. Add tests for backward compat mapping. Add tests for `maxTier()` derivation.\n   162→\n   163→### Acceptance Criteria\n   164→\n   165→- [ ] AC1: Given `VerificationTier` type, when inspected, then it's `'test-provable' | 'runtime-provable' | 'environment-provable' | 'escalate'`\n   166→- [ ] AC2: Given an AC tagged `<!-- verification: test-provable -->`, when story tier is derived, then story uses test-provable verification (no Docker)\n   167→- [ ] AC3: Given a story with 5 `test-provable` ACs and 1 `runtime-provable` AC, when story tier is derived, then it's `runtime-provable` (highest wins)\n   168→- [ ] AC4: Given an AC tagged with old format `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->`, when parsed, then it maps to `test-provable` (backward compat)\n   169→- [ ] AC5: Given `classifyTier(\"Given function X exists\")`, when called, then returns `'test-provable'`\n   170→- [ ] AC6: Given `classifyTier(\"Given the CLI outputs JSON\")`, when called, then returns `'runtime-provable'`\n   171→- [ ] AC7: Given `classifyTier(\"Given logs appear in VictoriaLogs\")`, when called, then returns `'environment-provable'`\n   172→- [ ] AC8: Given `classifyTier(\"Given 60fps on physical display\")`, when called, then returns `'escalate'`\n   173→- [ ] AC9: Given harness-run Step 3d, when story tier is `test-provable`, then verification runs via subagent with build+test+code-inspection only\n   174→- [ ] AC10: Given harness-run Step 3d, when story tier is `environment-provable`, then full Docker verification flow runs\n   175→- [ ] AC11: Given create-story prompt in Step 3a, when agent creates ACs, then each AC has `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag with one of the four tiers\n   176→- [ ] AC12: Given all changes, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass with 0 regressions\n   177→\n   178→## Additional Context\n   179→\n   180→### Dependencies\n   181→- No new npm dependencies.\n   182→\n   183→### Testing Strategy\n   184→- Update all `classifyStrategy` tests to `classifyTier` with new tier values\n   185→- Add backward compat tests for old tag formats\n   186→- Add `maxTier()` derivation tests\n   187→- Proof validation tests for all four tier names\n   188→\n   189→### Notes\n   190→- **Backward compat is cheap:** Old tags map to new tiers in one function. No story file migration.\n   191→- **`runtime-provable` is new territory.** Currently nothing handles \"run the binary locally.\" The subagent prompt needs to know how to build and run the project (cargo run, npm start, python main.py). The stack provider's `getBuildCommands()` / `getTestCommands()` already exist — extend with `getRunCommand()`.\n   192→- **Most codeharness stories are `test-provable`.** The analysis showed 60% of verification cost was Docker, but most stories just needed build+test. Proper tier classification will save significant tokens.\n   193→- **StackProvider needs `getRunCommand()`.** Currently has `getBuildCommands()` and `getTestCommands()` but no run command. For `runtime-provable` verification, the subagent needs to know how to start the app (e.g., `cargo run`, `npm start`, `python -m app`). Add `getRunCommand?(): string[]` as optional method to StackProvider interface — not all stacks have a runnable artifact (libraries don't).\n   194→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017T6a4hLkrgVbCgAqvDRzfv","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"d8612e81-feda-4b85-836c-5f11545231b9","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:00:04.372Z"}
