{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019KtLs75msF2eAzFxBUpNa1","type":"tool_result","content":"   140→> - `codeharness progress --clear` ONCE per story, not twice\n   141→> - Timestamps: use the current time from your system prompt, don't shell out to `date`\n   142→> - Don't re-read files that haven't changed since last read\n   143→\n   144→**Live progress updates:** Before executing each sub-step (3a/3b/3c/3d), update sprint-state.json with the current progress:\n   145→\n   146→```bash\n   147→codeharness progress --story {story_key} --phase {create|dev|review|verify} --action \"Starting {step description}\"\n   148→```\n   149→\n   150→This enables external tools to see what the session is doing in real time.\n   151→\n   152→### 3a: If status is `backlog` — Run Create Story\n   153→\n   154→Invoke the create-story workflow via Agent tool to generate the story file:\n   155→\n   156→```\n   157→Use the Agent tool with:\n   158→  prompt: \"Run /create-story for story {story_key}. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   159→\n   160→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n   161→- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n   162→- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n   163→- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n   164→- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\n   165→If nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n   166→\n   167→MANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   168→- Total tool calls: N\n   169→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017T6a4hLkrgVbCgAqvDRzfv","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"f9549679-e8c7-448e-aefa-b651cd5b56f4","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:00:33.545Z"}
