{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LGQEdJrC6UKWDTxZGah1ph","type":"tool_result","content":"   450→   ```markdown\n   451→   ## Verification Findings\n   452→\n   453→   _Last updated: {timestamp}_\n   454→\n   455→   The following ACs failed black-box verification:\n   456→\n   457→   ### AC {N}: {description}\n   458→   **Verdict:** FAIL\n   459→   **Error output:**\n   460→   ```\n   461→   {relevant error output from proof}\n   462→   ```\n   463→\n   464→   {repeat for each failing AC}\n   465→   ```\n   466→\n   467→3. **Increment `attempts`.** If `attempts >= max_attempts` (10):\n   468→   - Increment `stories_skipped`\n   469→   - Append `{story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit (10)` to `skipped_reasons`\n   470→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit reached — skipping`\n   471→   - Run cleanup (step 3d-viii)\n   472→   - Go to Step 2 (next story)\n   473→\n   474→4. **Return story to dev.** Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status from `verifying` to `in-progress`.\n   475→\n   476→5. **Reset retry count.** Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}=0` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This resets the infra retry budget since the story is going back to dev.\n   477→\n   478→6. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verification found {N} failing ACs — returning to dev (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   479→\n   480→7. Run cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   481→\n   482→8. Go to Step 3b (dev-story) — the story is now `in-progress` and the dev prompt will include the verification findings.\n   483→\n   484→**Path B — Infrastructure failures (timeout, docker error, no proof produced, verifier non-zero exit WITHOUT a proof):**\n   485→\n   486→The verification could not complete due to infrastructure issues — NOT code quality.\n   487→\n   488→**Before retrying blindly, diagnose the infra problem:**\n   489→\n   490→1. Read the verifier output/error. Identify what specifically failed:\n   491→   - Container missing the project binary? → Fix `Dockerfile.verify` or `verify-env prepare` to install it correctly\n   492→   - Tree-shaking removed needed code from dist/? → Add the entry point to tsup config or create a CLI command that exposes the functionality\n   493→   - Wrong version of tool in container? → Fix the Docker image build to use local dist/\n   494→   - Port conflict? → Fix shared stack detection\n   495→   - Container didn't start? → Fix Docker configuration\n   496→\n   497→2. **Fix the infrastructure problem** by modifying the relevant files (Dockerfile, verify-env, tsup config, docker-compose). This is a code change — commit it.\n   498→\n   499→3. Rebuild: `npm run build`\n   500→\n   501→4. Retry verification with the fixed infrastructure.\n   502→\n   503→5. If after 3 infra fix attempts the problem persists, increment `attempts` and move to next story:\n   504→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: infra problem persists after 3 fix attempts — skipping (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   505→   - Go to Step 2\n   506→\n   507→**The agent must NOT repeatedly retry the same broken infrastructure.** Each retry must include an actual fix attempt.\n   508→\n   509→**Path C — Escalated ACs due to infra/tooling problems:**\n   510→\n   511→An AC was marked `[ESCALATE]` but the reason is infrastructure, not impossibility. Fix the infrastructure:\n   512→\n   513→1. Identify the infra problem from the escalation reason (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker config, etc.)\n   514→2. Fix the root cause — modify Dockerfile, tsup config, verify-env, or whatever is broken\n   515→3. Delete the existing proof: `rm verification/{story_key}-proof.md`\n   516→4. Return story to `verifying` and re-run verification from step 3d-i\n   517→5. Do NOT accept infra problems as valid escalations\n   518→\n   519→**3d-viii: Cleanup (unconditional — runs on both success and failure)**\n   520→\n   521→```bash\n   522→codeharness verify-env cleanup --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   523→```\n   524→\n   525→This removes the temp workspace at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` and stops/removes the Docker container. This step MUST run even if verification failed — leaked containers and temp directories accumulate.\n   526→\n   527→If cleanup fails, log a warning but continue:\n   528→```\n   529→[WARN] verify-env cleanup failed for {story_key}: {error}\n   530→```\n   531→\n   532→### 3e: Sync Beads Status\n   533→\n   534→After the story reaches `done`, sync the status to beads (if initialized):\n   535→\n   536→```bash\n   537→codeharness sync --story {story_key} --direction files-to-beads\n   538→```\n   539→\n   540→If this fails, log a warning but continue — beads sync is not a blocking step:\n   541→```\n   542→[WARN] Beads sync failed for {story_key}: {error message}\n   543→```\n   544→\n   545→### 3f: Commit Story Changes\n   546→\n   547→After the story reaches `done`, commit all changes with a coherent message.\n   548→\n   549→1. Stage all changes: `git add -A`\n   550→2. Commit with message: `feat: story {story_key} — {short title from story file}`\n   551→3. The commit must include source code, tests, story file, sprint-status.yaml, proof document, and any other changed files\n   552→4. If `git commit` fails (e.g., pre-commit hooks), log the error and continue — do not halt the sprint:\n   553→   ```\n   554→   [WARN] git commit failed for story {story_key}: {error message}\n   555→   ```\n   556→\n   557→## Step 4: Story Complete — Continue or Finish Epic\n   558→\n   559→A story just completed successfully. Clear live run progress immediately:\n   560→\n   561→```bash\n   562→codeharness progress --clear\n   563→```\n   564→\n   565→1. Increment `stories_completed`\n   566→2. Re-read `sprint-status.yaml` to get current state\n   567→3. Determine the story's parent epic (epic number N from the story key)\n   568→4. Check if all stories in epic N are `done` (every `N-M-slug` has status `done`):\n   569→   - If yes → go to Step 5 (epic completion). After Step 5, return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan.\n   570→   - If no → go directly to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan (attempts will be reset there for the new story)\n   571→\n   572→## Step 5: Epic Completion\n   573→\n   574→All stories in the current epic are done.\n   575→\n   576→1. Check if `epic-{N}-retrospective` entry exists and status is `optional`:\n   577→   - If yes, run the retrospective:\n   578→     ```\n   579→     Use the Agent tool with:\n   580→       prompt: \"Run /retrospective for Epic {N}. All stories are complete. Review the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   581→\n   582→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n   583→- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n   584→- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n   585→- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n   586→- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\n   587→If nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n   588→\n   589→MANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   590→- Total tool calls: N\n   591→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n   592→- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n   593→- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n   594→- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls\"\n   595→       subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   596→     ```\n   597→   - After retrospective completes:\n   598→     a. Update `epic-{N}-retrospective` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool — do NOT rely on the retro agent to do this)\n   599→     b. Verify the update was applied\n   600→\n   601→2. Update `epic-{N}` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool)\n   602→\n   603→3. Commit epic completion: `git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: epic {N} complete\"`\n   604→   - If `git commit` fails, log the error and continue:\n   605→     ```\n   606→     [WARN] git commit failed for epic {N}: {error message}\n   607→     ```\n   608→\n   609→4. Print:\n   610→   ```\n   611→   [OK] Epic {N}: DONE (all stories complete, retrospective run)\n   612→   ```\n   613→\n   614→5. Return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan. Step 2 will determine if more actionable stories exist or if the sprint is complete.\n   615→\n   616→## Step 6: Failure Handling\n   617→\n   618→A story has exceeded max_attempts (10). Clear live run progress immediately:\n   619→\n   620→```bash\n   621→codeharness progress --clear\n   622→```\n   623→\n   624→1. Increment `stories_failed`\n   625→2. Increment `stories_skipped`\n   626→3. Append `{story_key}: failed ({reason})` to `skipped_reasons` where reason is `retry-exhausted` or `max-cycles-exceeded`\n   627→4. Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}={attempts}` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This persists the retry state so future sessions skip this story immediately via the retry-exhausted check in Step 2.\n   628→5. Print:\n   629→   ```\n   630→   [FAIL] Story {story_key}: exceeded {max_attempts} attempts\n   631→   [FAIL] Last status: {current_status}\n   632→   [INFO] Skipping story — continuing to next actionable story\n   633→   ```\n   634→6. Go to Step 2 to find the next actionable story. Do NOT halt the sprint. Step 2 will go to Step 7 only when zero actionable stories remain.\n   635→\n   636→## Step 7: Sprint Execution Summary\n   637→\n   638→Clear live run progress to ensure clean state before printing summary:\n   639→\n   640→```bash\n   641→codeharness progress --clear\n   642→```\n   643→\n   644→Print the final summary:\n   645→\n   646→```\n   647→━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n   648→Harness Run — Sprint Execution Complete\n   649→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WTx8j9hk9cZfjCVrJFg5MD","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"696b5aa9-bed0-4f56-9801-b68a135e067d","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:03:58.838Z"}
