{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016n4T9DeNHE8Ph6y6azPGMJ","type":"tool_result","content":"   300→5. For each AC in the story file, verify it:\n   301→   - File existence: ls path/to/file\n   302→   - Exports: grep 'export' path/to/file\n   303→   - Function existence: grep 'function name' path/to/file\n   304→   - Test output: check relevant test names in output\n   305→   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n   306→6. Generate proof document at verification/{story_key}-proof.md with evidence from each check.\n   307→7. Run codeharness verify --story {story_key} to validate the proof format.\n   308→8. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n   309→\n   310→Do NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   311→\n   312→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   313→- Total tool calls: N\n   314→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n   315→- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n   316→- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n   317→- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls\"\n   318→  subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   319→```\n   320→\n   321→After the subagent returns:\n   322→1. Extract the `## Token Report` section and append to `.session-issues.md`\n   323→2. Parse the result: ALL_PASS → mark story `done`. PARTIAL → treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n   324→3. **No Docker involved at any point.** Skip steps 3d-i through 3d-viii entirely.\n   325→\n   326→**runtime-provable verification (derived tier = runtime-provable):**\n   327→\n   328→Use a **single subagent** for the entire verification. Build the project, then run it locally — no Docker stack needed.\n   329→\n   330→```\n   331→Use the Agent tool with:\n   332→  prompt: \"Verify story {story_key} using local runtime checks (runtime-provable tier).\n   333→\n   334→Story file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md\n   335→\n   336→Execute these steps and report results:\n   337→1. Run the project build command (npm run build, cargo build, etc). Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n   338→2. Run tests (npm test, cargo test, etc). Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n   339→3. Detect the project stack and determine the run command:\n   340→   - Node.js: npm start, or node dist/index.js, or npx ts-node src/index.ts\n   341→   - Rust: cargo run\n   342→   - Python: python -m app, or python main.py\n   343→   Check package.json scripts, Cargo.toml, or setup.py for clues.\n   344→4. Start the application in the background. Wait up to 10 seconds for it to be ready.\n   345→5. For each AC in the story file, verify it by interacting with the running app:\n   346→   - CLI apps: run with flags/args, check stdout/stderr/exit code\n   347→   - HTTP apps: curl localhost:{port}/endpoint, check response status and body\n   348→   - Check process behavior: signals, graceful shutdown, file output\n   349→   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n   350→6. Kill the running application process (kill PID or ctrl-C equivalent).\n   351→7. Generate proof document at verification/{story_key}-proof.md with evidence from each check.\n   352→8. Run codeharness verify --story {story_key} to validate the proof format.\n   353→9. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n   354→\n   355→Do NOT use Docker. Do NOT run codeharness stack start. Do NOT start Docker containers.\n   356→Do NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   357→\n   358→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   359→- Total tool calls: N\n   360→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n   361→- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n   362→- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n   363→- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls\"\n   364→  subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   365→```\n   366→\n   367→After the subagent returns:\n   368→1. Extract the `## Token Report` section and append to `.session-issues.md`\n   369→2. Parse the result: ALL_PASS → mark story `done`. PARTIAL → treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n   370→3. **No Docker involved at any point.** Skip steps 3d-i through 3d-viii entirely.\n   371→\n   372→**escalate verification (derived tier = escalate):**\n   373→\n   374→When the derived tier is `escalate`, at least one AC requires human judgment or external services. Use mixed-tier dispatch:\n   375→\n   376→1. Re-read the story file. For each AC, extract its individual `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag (with legacy mapping as in Step 3d-0).\n   377→2. Group ACs by their individual tier:\n   378→   - `escalate`-tier ACs: mark each as `[ESCALATE]` in the proof document with the reason \"Requires human judgment or external service — cannot be automated.\"\n   379→   - All other ACs: dispatch verification at their individual tier level. Use the corresponding subagent prompt (test-provable, runtime-provable, or environment-provable) to verify those ACs specifically.\n   380→3. Generate proof document at `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. Include:\n   381→   - PASS/FAIL verdict for each non-escalated AC (with evidence)\n   382→   - `[ESCALATE]` verdict for each escalated AC (with reason)\n   383→4. Run `codeharness verify --story {story_key}` to validate the proof format.\n   384→5. If all non-escalated ACs pass: mark story `done` with escalation notes. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`.\n   385→6. If any non-escalated AC fails: treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n   386→\n   387→**environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable):** Full Docker container with no source code access.\n   388→\n   389→**No internal timeout.** Verification takes as long as it takes. Ralph's iteration timeout is the safety net.\n   390→\n   391→**Pre-verification: Read retry state from `ralph/.story_retries`.**\n   392→\n   393→Read the file `ralph/.story_retries`. If the file contains a line matching `{story_key}={N}`, set `attempts = N`. If no matching line exists, set `attempts = 0`. This ensures retry budgets persist across sessions.\n   394→\n   395→**Pre-verification: Check observability infrastructure.**\n   396→\n   397→```bash\n   398→codeharness status --check-docker 2>&1\n   399→```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0116QeEpK9QPXZrqFgqyf1PK","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"dd05ed05-c5b5-42f0-ae5e-a4363dbdce1f","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:12:02.508Z"}
