{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X7qX68U5QToLhD6XusUDxN","type":"tool_result","content":"   400→\n   401→If the output indicates the observability stack is down:\n   402→```bash\n   403→codeharness stack start 2>&1\n   404→```\n   405→\n   406→If `codeharness stack start` fails, log `[FAIL] Observability stack failed to start — cannot verify` and go to Step 6 (failure handling).\n   407→\n   408→**Pre-verification: Build dist/.**\n   409→\n   410→```bash\n   411→npm run build 2>&1\n   412→```\n   413→\n   414→If the build fails, fix errors before proceeding. The Docker image needs current dist/.\n   415→\n   416→**Verification flow — execute these steps sequentially:**\n   417→\n   418→**3d-i: Build Docker verify image**\n   419→\n   420→```bash\n   421→codeharness verify-env build 2>&1\n   422→```\n   423→\n   424→If this fails:\n   425→```\n   426→[FAIL] verify-env build failed: {error}\n   427→```\n   428→Leave story at `verifying`, go to Step 6. No fallback.\n   429→\n   430→**3d-ii: Start Docker container**\n   431→\n   432→```bash\n   433→docker run -d --name codeharness-verify --network host \\\n   434→  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\" \\\n   435→  codeharness-verify sleep infinity\n   436→```\n   437→\n   438→`--network host` allows the container to reach OTEL Collector at `localhost:4318`, VictoriaLogs at `:9428`, VictoriaMetrics at `:8428`, and VictoriaTraces at `:16686`. The `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var enables the `claude` CLI inside the container for verifier sessions that need to spawn Claude subprocesses.\n   439→\n   440→If `docker run` fails, log `[FAIL] docker run failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to Step 6. No cleanup needed — the container never started.\n   441→\n   442→**3d-iii: Prepare clean workspace**\n   443→\n   444→```bash\n   445→codeharness verify-env prepare --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   446→```\n   447→\n   448→This creates `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` with built artifacts, docs, and story file — but NO source code.\n   449→\n   450→If this fails, log `[FAIL] verify-env prepare failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to cleanup (step 3d-viii) then Step 6. The container is running and must be cleaned up.\n   451→\n   452→**3d-iv: Run verifier session**\n   453→\n   454→Build the verification prompt and spawn the verifier:\n   455→\n   456→1. Read the story content from `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/story.md`\n   457→2. Read the prompt template from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — use `verifyPromptTemplate()` with the story content, container name `codeharness-verify`, and default observability endpoints\n   458→3. Run the verifier:\n   459→\n   460→```bash\n   461→cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key} && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"{verification_prompt}\"\n   462→```\n   463→\n   464→The prompt (from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`) instructs the verifier that:\n   465→\n   466→- It has **NO source code access** — `src/` does not exist in the workspace\n   467→- **ALL CLI commands** must run via `docker exec codeharness-verify <command>`\n   468→- It should read `README.md` for usage guidance\n   469→- It should query observability endpoints from the host:\n   470→  - VictoriaLogs: `http://localhost:9428`\n   471→  - VictoriaMetrics: `http://localhost:8428`\n   472→  - VictoriaTraces: `http://localhost:16686`\n   473→- The proof document goes in `verification/{story_key}-proof.md` within the clean workspace\n   474→- REAL failures must be reported — never fabricate evidence\n   475→- ACs that cannot be verified should be marked `[ESCALATE]`\n   476→\n   477→If the verifier process exits non-zero or times out, treat as failure (proceed to retry logic in step 3d-vii).\n   478→\n   479→**3d-v: Copy proof document back**\n   480→\n   481→```bash\n   482→cp /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/verification/{story_key}-proof.md verification/\n   483→```\n   484→\n   485→If the proof file does not exist (verifier crashed or failed to produce one), treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   486→\n   487→**3d-vi: Validate proof quality**\n   488→\n   489→```bash\n   490→codeharness verify --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   491→```\n   492→\n   493→Parse the output/exit code. After parsing each AC verdict from the proof, update the live progress:\n   494→\n   495→```bash\n   496→codeharness progress --ac-progress \"{passed}/{total}\"\n   497→```\n   498→\n   499→where `passed` is ACs with PASS verdict and `total` is all ACs.\n   500→\n   501→- If `pending === 0` and `escalated === 0` → proof quality passed. Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status to `done`. Print: `[OK] Story {story_key}: verifying → done`. Proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   502→- If `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` → verifier could not reach some ACs. **Before accepting escalation, diagnose WHY:**\n   503→  1. Read the proof document. For each `[ESCALATE]` AC, check the reason.\n   504→  2. **If the reason is infrastructure/tooling** (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker not configured, wrong version installed): this is NOT a valid escalation. The infrastructure needs fixing. Treat as **Path C** below.\n   505→  3. **If the reason is genuinely impossible to automate** (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment): accept the escalation. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} genuinely escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`. Update status to `done`.\n   506→  4. **Do NOT leave stories at `verifying` with escalated ACs.** Either fix the infra problem (Path C) or accept and mark done.\n   507→- If `pending > 0` → proof has gaps. Treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   508→\n   509→If the verifier made code fixes (detected by checking `git diff` after verification), run:\n   510→```bash\n   511→npm run build && npm run test:unit\n   512→```\n   513→to confirm fixes haven't broken anything. Then proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   514→\n   515→**3d-vii: Failure handling — code bugs vs infrastructure failures**\n   516→\n   517→Determine the failure type. There are two distinct paths:\n   518→\n   519→**Path A — Code bugs (`pending > 0` in proof validation):**\n   520→\n   521→A proof document exists and `codeharness verify` reported `pending > 0`. This means the feature has real bugs — the code does not satisfy the ACs. Code bugs NEVER count against the retry budget.\n   522→\n   523→1. **Extract failing ACs from the proof document.** Read `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. For each AC section (`## AC N: description`), check if the verdict is not PASS and not `[ESCALATE]`. For each failing AC, extract:\n   524→   - The AC number and description (from the `## AC N:` heading)\n   525→   - The error output (from the `output` code blocks and any verdict text)\n   526→\n   527→2. **Save findings to the story file.** Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md`. If it already has a `## Verification Findings` section, replace that section entirely with the new findings. If not, append a new `## Verification Findings` section before the `## Dev Agent Record` section (or at the end if that section doesn't exist). Format:\n   528→   ```markdown\n   529→   ## Verification Findings\n   530→\n   531→   _Last updated: {timestamp}_\n   532→\n   533→   The following ACs failed black-box verification:\n   534→\n   535→   ### AC {N}: {description}\n   536→   **Verdict:** FAIL\n   537→   **Error output:**\n   538→   ```\n   539→   {relevant error output from proof}\n   540→   ```\n   541→\n   542→   {repeat for each failing AC}\n   543→   ```\n   544→\n   545→3. **Increment `attempts`.** If `attempts >= max_attempts` (10):\n   546→   - Increment `stories_skipped`\n   547→   - Append `{story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit (10)` to `skipped_reasons`\n   548→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit reached — skipping`\n   549→   - Run cleanup (step 3d-viii)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0116QeEpK9QPXZrqFgqyf1PK","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"8ab509f1-520b-4d06-a139-fc9cccc2e0a3","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:12:06.484Z"}
