{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FSQEQkHPGnkFeh2mjSsJbr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018zBdSR1qXgiHj4xaukzuZC","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/commands/harness-run.md","offset":550,"limit":150},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4628,"cache_read_input_tokens":36941,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4628,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":71,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0116QeEpK9QPXZrqFgqyf1PK","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"d4427e27-40be-46b1-b10d-3d6f44fc98c3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018zBdSR1qXgiHj4xaukzuZC","type":"tool_result","content":"   550→   - Go to Step 2 (next story)\n   551→\n   552→4. **Return story to dev.** Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status from `verifying` to `in-progress`.\n   553→\n   554→5. **Reset retry count.** Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}=0` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This resets the infra retry budget since the story is going back to dev.\n   555→\n   556→6. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verification found {N} failing ACs — returning to dev (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   557→\n   558→7. Run cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   559→\n   560→8. Go to Step 3b (dev-story) — the story is now `in-progress` and the dev prompt will include the verification findings.\n   561→\n   562→**Path B — Infrastructure failures (timeout, docker error, no proof produced, verifier non-zero exit WITHOUT a proof):**\n   563→\n   564→The verification could not complete due to infrastructure issues — NOT code quality.\n   565→\n   566→**Before retrying blindly, diagnose the infra problem:**\n   567→\n   568→1. Read the verifier output/error. Identify what specifically failed:\n   569→   - Container missing the project binary? → Fix `Dockerfile.verify` or `verify-env prepare` to install it correctly\n   570→   - Tree-shaking removed needed code from dist/? → Add the entry point to tsup config or create a CLI command that exposes the functionality\n   571→   - Wrong version of tool in container? → Fix the Docker image build to use local dist/\n   572→   - Port conflict? → Fix shared stack detection\n   573→   - Container didn't start? → Fix Docker configuration\n   574→\n   575→2. **Fix the infrastructure problem** by modifying the relevant files (Dockerfile, verify-env, tsup config, docker-compose). This is a code change — commit it.\n   576→\n   577→3. Rebuild: `npm run build`\n   578→\n   579→4. Retry verification with the fixed infrastructure.\n   580→\n   581→5. If after 3 infra fix attempts the problem persists, increment `attempts` and move to next story:\n   582→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: infra problem persists after 3 fix attempts — skipping (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   583→   - Go to Step 2\n   584→\n   585→**The agent must NOT repeatedly retry the same broken infrastructure.** Each retry must include an actual fix attempt.\n   586→\n   587→**Path C — Escalated ACs due to infra/tooling problems:**\n   588→\n   589→An AC was marked `[ESCALATE]` but the reason is infrastructure, not impossibility. Fix the infrastructure:\n   590→\n   591→1. Identify the infra problem from the escalation reason (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker config, etc.)\n   592→2. Fix the root cause — modify Dockerfile, tsup config, verify-env, or whatever is broken\n   593→3. Delete the existing proof: `rm verification/{story_key}-proof.md`\n   594→4. Return story to `verifying` and re-run verification from step 3d-i\n   595→5. Do NOT accept infra problems as valid escalations\n   596→\n   597→**3d-viii: Cleanup (unconditional — runs on both success and failure)**\n   598→\n   599→```bash\n   600→codeharness verify-env cleanup --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   601→```\n   602→\n   603→This removes the temp workspace at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` and stops/removes the Docker container. This step MUST run even if verification failed — leaked containers and temp directories accumulate.\n   604→\n   605→If cleanup fails, log a warning but continue:\n   606→```\n   607→[WARN] verify-env cleanup failed for {story_key}: {error}\n   608→```\n   609→\n   610→### 3e: Sync Beads Status\n   611→\n   612→After the story reaches `done`, sync the status to beads (if initialized):\n   613→\n   614→```bash\n   615→codeharness sync --story {story_key} --direction files-to-beads\n   616→```\n   617→\n   618→If this fails, log a warning but continue — beads sync is not a blocking step:\n   619→```\n   620→[WARN] Beads sync failed for {story_key}: {error message}\n   621→```\n   622→\n   623→### 3f: Commit Story Changes\n   624→\n   625→After the story reaches `done`, commit all changes with a coherent message.\n   626→\n   627→1. Stage all changes: `git add -A`\n   628→2. Commit with message: `feat: story {story_key} — {short title from story file}`\n   629→3. The commit must include source code, tests, story file, sprint-status.yaml, proof document, and any other changed files\n   630→4. If `git commit` fails (e.g., pre-commit hooks), log the error and continue — do not halt the sprint:\n   631→   ```\n   632→   [WARN] git commit failed for story {story_key}: {error message}\n   633→   ```\n   634→\n   635→## Step 4: Story Complete — Continue or Finish Epic\n   636→\n   637→A story just completed successfully. Clear live run progress immediately:\n   638→\n   639→```bash\n   640→codeharness progress --clear\n   641→```\n   642→\n   643→1. Increment `stories_completed`\n   644→2. Re-read `sprint-status.yaml` to get current state\n   645→3. Determine the story's parent epic (epic number N from the story key)\n   646→4. Check if all stories in epic N are `done` (every `N-M-slug` has status `done`):\n   647→   - If yes → go to Step 5 (epic completion). After Step 5, return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan.\n   648→   - If no → go directly to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan (attempts will be reset there for the new story)\n   649→\n   650→## Step 5: Epic Completion\n   651→\n   652→All stories in the current epic are done.\n   653→\n   654→1. Check if `epic-{N}-retrospective` entry exists and status is `optional`:\n   655→   - If yes, run the retrospective:\n   656→     ```\n   657→     Use the Agent tool with:\n   658→       prompt: \"Run /retrospective for Epic {N}. All stories are complete. Review the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   659→\n   660→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n   661→- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n   662→- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n   663→- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n   664→- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\n   665→If nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n   666→\n   667→MANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   668→- Total tool calls: N\n   669→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n   670→- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n   671→- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n   672→- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls\"\n   673→       subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   674→     ```\n   675→   - After retrospective completes:\n   676→     a. Update `epic-{N}-retrospective` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool — do NOT rely on the retro agent to do this)\n   677→     b. Verify the update was applied\n   678→\n   679→2. Update `epic-{N}` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool)\n   680→\n   681→3. Commit epic completion: `git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: epic {N} complete\"`\n   682→   - If `git commit` fails, log the error and continue:\n   683→     ```\n   684→     [WARN] git commit failed for epic {N}: {error message}\n   685→     ```\n   686→\n   687→4. Print:\n   688→   ```\n   689→   [OK] Epic {N}: DONE (all stories complete, retrospective run)\n   690→   ```\n   691→\n   692→5. Return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan. Step 2 will determine if more actionable stories exist or if the sprint is complete.\n   693→\n   694→## Step 6: Failure Handling\n   695→\n   696→A story has exceeded max_attempts (10). Clear live run progress immediately:\n   697→\n   698→```bash\n   699→codeharness progress --clear"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0116QeEpK9QPXZrqFgqyf1PK","session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"e518d5a7-5c5c-4d05-8653-23392c82fb30","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:12:10.990Z"}
