{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0116QeEpK9QPXZrqFgqyf1PK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md\n**Status:** review -> verifying\n\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 1 Medium, 2 Low\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH — Missing `## Session Issues` in test-provable subagent prompt.** The test-provable verification subagent prompt (lines ~310-318) only had `## Token Report` but was missing the mandatory `## Session Issues` section that every other subagent prompt includes. Fixed by adding the section with verification-appropriate issue categories.\n\n2. **HIGH — Missing `## Session Issues` in runtime-provable subagent prompt.** Same issue in the runtime-provable subagent prompt (lines ~365-371). Fixed with runtime-appropriate issue categories (port conflicts, app startup failures, etc.).\n\n3. **MEDIUM — Missing Docker cleanup guidance in escalate dispatch.** The escalate section dispatches non-escalated ACs at their individual tier level, which may include environment-provable (Docker). But it had no mention of running cleanup (step 3d-viii) after Docker-based sub-verification completes. Fixed by adding step 7 referencing cleanup.\n\nAlso fixed in both subagent \"After the subagent returns\" sections: changed \"Extract the `## Token Report`\" to \"Extract both `## Session Issues` and `## Token Report`\" to match the new mandatory sections.\n\n### Test Results\n\n- 34/34 dispatch tests pass\n- 3926/3926 full suite tests pass\n- Coverage: 96.86% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: test-provable subagent prompt missing `## Session Issues` mandatory section (inconsistent with all other subagent prompts in the file)\n- HIGH: runtime-provable subagent prompt missing `## Session Issues` mandatory section (same inconsistency)\n- MEDIUM: escalate dispatch missing Docker cleanup guidance when environment-provable sub-verification is used\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- LOW: The escalate section has no subagent prompt wrapper — it's inline instructions. All other tier dispatches use subagent prompts. This inconsistency means escalate verification runs in the parent context, consuming tokens. Future story should wrap it in a subagent.\n- LOW: Tests are pure string-containment assertions against markdown. While appropriate for a prompt-engineering story, they're brittle — any rewording of the prompts will break them. Consider moving key strings to constants or using regex patterns.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No coverage gaps — all 158 files above 80%, overall 96.86%.\n- The test file tests for string presence but doesn't test the *ordering* of dispatch sections (e.g., test-provable before runtime-provable before escalate before environment-provable). Order matters for prompt interpretation.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The escalate flow says \"dispatch verification at their individual tier level\" but doesn't specify *how* — does the orchestrator run separate subagents for each tier group? Or one subagent that handles all non-escalated ACs? This ambiguity could lead to inconsistent behavior across LLM sessions.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git diff -- commands/harness-run.md` (~100 lines), `npx vitest run` (~30 lines), `npx codeharness coverage --min-file 80` (~4 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 12 total reads (harness-run.md read 5 times across offset ranges)\n- Redundant operations: harness-run.md was read in 5 separate offset chunks — could have been more efficient with larger chunk sizes. Coverage was run twice (before and after fixes) which was necessary for verification."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a67ec46e754a24871 (use SendMessage with to: 'a67ec46e754a24871' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61083\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 296054</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9b706e3-1764-4868-a4a5-c90b37d26d0d","uuid":"567c9f74-b894-4479-9d29-afad9d6d36ab","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:15:56.207Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"a67ec46e754a24871","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md\n**Status:** review